name: Playtest 20151114
body:
We have received great feedback on our Halloween playtest and have been hard at work to resolve the issues that have been brought to our attention.

This release candidate includes more Dune 2000 polish and Red Alert balance changes, as well as copy & paste support in the map editor in addition to the usual round of bug fixes.

Please give this playtest a try. We're especially interested in feedback on balance. Check out the full releae announcement at http://openra.net and report any problems you encounter at https://bugs.openra.net. Thanks, and have fun!

name: Playtest 20151031
body:
Today we have started the countdown to our next stable release with a new OpenRA Halloween playtest!

Global lobby chat, game speed settings, balance changes, new missions, improved performance: we have all sorts of tricks and treats in store for you today!

Head over to our website at http://openra.net to read all about the good things coming your way, or read the detailed changelog at http://changelog.openra.net.

We rely on your feedback to make the next release as awesome as possible, so please give this playtest a try and report any and all problems you encounter at http://bugs.openra.net. Thanks, and have fun!

name: Release 20150614
body:
The newest incarnation of OpenRA is out now!

The standout feature of this release is no doubt the new in-game editor, which for the first time in OpenRA history offers fully cross-platform map editing abilities for all our supported mods. Other changes are all over the place: map chooser, new missions, new support power hotkeys, you name it!

Check out the full release announcement on http://openra.net and the changelog at http://changelog.openra.net to find out more about these and other shiny new things!

Download now and enjoy!

name: Release 20150424
body:
We are thrilled to announce the Spring release of OpenRA!

This release, almost six months in the making, is one of our biggest yet: it contains countless new features, bug fixes and improvements. Sandworms and Carryalls for Dune 2000 and playable Countries in Red Alert are the most visible enhancements, but there is lots more to discover!

Check out http://openra.net for the full announcement and http://changelog.openra.net for the complete changelog.

Enjoy and have a lot of fun! Thank you!

name: Playtest 20150328
body: Windows setup was unversioned, superseded by Playtest 20150329.

name: Playtest 20150118
body:
There is a new release on the horizon for which we have released the first playtest today.

The focus of improvements has been on the Dune 2000 mod, which most importantly now features
Sandworms and Carryalls. The biggest change in the Red Alert mod has been the addition of
playable country factions, each with its own special abilities. On top of that, the game has
received quite a number of performance improvements as well as the usual bug fixes and
polishing all over the place.

Please give this playtest a try and report any and all problems at http://bugs.openra.net.
Thank you, and happy new year!

name: Halloween 2014 Release
body:
After three months of unrelenting work, resulting in over 760 commits and over 100,000 changed lines by 41 contributors, we are proud to present to you this year's Halloween release!

All the changes are too numerous to mention in this little space, but you'll surely notice an improved user interface, both in and out of the game, greater stability and lots of gameplay polishing.  Please see our changelog at http://changelog.openra.net for a complete list.

We hope you enjoy this release, and wish you a happy Halloween!

name: Playtest 20141020
body:
Hot on the heels of last week's, we have released the final playtest in preparation for our next stable release.

This playtest improves memory usage, corrects a long-standing bug with crushing fences, among others, introduces an overhauled observer and replay sidebar, and sees more work towards the single-player campaigns.  The new Lua API has gained another set of improvements and is finally able to completely replace the old API, which has now been removed.

Please take this playtest out for a spin and report any and all problems at http://bugs.openra.net.

name: Halloween 2014 RC 2
body:
We are making big strides towards our upcoming Halloween release, for which we have now released a second playtest.

On top of all the bug fixes and improvements of the previous playtest, this one adds more stability, UI polish and gameplay improvements. On the modding front, our new Lua API has again been the focus of attention, and also some gaps in our trait documentation have been closed, amonst others.  Please see the changelog on our wiki for a full list.

As always, please give this playtest a try and report any and all problems you encounter at http://bugs.openra.net.

https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRAWeb/pull/162

name: Playtest 20140927
body:
The first playtest for our next big release is now available!

The biggest change in this playtest compared to our July release is the overhauled in-game interface.  Players will enjoy the new plane separation behaviour, balancing updates and updated campaign missions, while a heavily improved Lua API, mission objectives, a prerequisites system and unit upgrades will bring benefits to mappers and modders.

Please give this playtest a try and report any and all problems you encounter at http://bugs.openra.net

https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRAWeb/pull/159

name: Playtest 20140719 (July RC4)
body: Fixes a few more bugs in preparation for our July release.

name: Playtest 20140718 (July RC3)
body: Fixes a few remaining bugs in preparation for our July release.
